<task id="AUTHV2-040" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Rotate AzureAd + AgentToken client secrets to Key Vault references</title>
    <phase>C — Server hardening</phase>
    <tags>auth, server, security, secrets, FULL</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>Phase A</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false (coordinated deploy)</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Current state: AzureAd__ClientSecret and AgentToken__ClientSecret are plain values in App Service config (resource spe-api-dev-67e2xz, RG spe-infrastructure-westus2). Rotate them in Azure AD app registration, store new values in Key Vault, replace App Service config entries with @Microsoft.KeyVault(SecretUri=...) references. Coordinate brief App Service restart.

    The PRIOR secret value was exposed in tool output during the audit and MUST be treated as compromised.
  </prompt>
  <role>DevOps + security engineer with Azure access.</role>
  <goal>Both secrets rotated. App Service config has only Key Vault references. App restarts cleanly. Health checks pass.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.template.json (Key Vault ref pattern for Dataverse:ClientSecret as model)</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §3 C-1 (this exact finding)</file>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/ (Key Vault Bicep modules if applicable)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>In Azure portal (or via az ad app credential reset): generate new secret for BFF app registration `1e40baad-...`. Note: also for AgentToken if it's a separate registration.</step>
    <step>Store new secret(s) in Key Vault as `BFF-API-ClientSecret` (or use existing name if already in template).</step>
    <step>Update App Service config (via az webapp config appsettings set): replace plain `AzureAd__ClientSecret` and `AgentToken__ClientSecret` values with `@Microsoft.KeyVault(SecretUri=https://spe-keyvault-dev.vault.azure.net/secrets/BFF-API-ClientSecret/)`.</step>
    <step>Verify App Service managed identity has Key Vault Reader + Secrets Get permission.</step>
    <step>Restart App Service. Watch health endpoint (`/healthz`) come back online (may take 30-300s).</step>
    <step>Verify BFF can still authenticate to Dataverse + Graph (test by hitting an authenticated endpoint).</step>
    <step>Disable/delete old secret in Azure AD app registration.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>`az webapp config appsettings list` shows Key Vault reference syntax for both secrets, NOT plain values.</criterion>
    <criterion>App Service started successfully after restart.</criterion>
    <criterion>Health endpoint returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion>Authenticated BFF endpoint test succeeds.</criterion>
    <criterion>Old secret removed from Azure AD.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
